message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper presents a system for automatic quantification of calcium score in cardiac CT images using a supervised deep learning algorithm, specifically a convolutional neural network (CNN). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning and medical imaging suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), medical imaging (cs.MED), and neural networks (cs.NEURON) sub-categories.
